{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "{PROJECT_NAME} FAANGAI GitHub Sync",
  "description": "Sync FAANGAI specifications with GitHub issues and project boards",
  "version": "1.0",
  "when": {
    "type": "fileEdited",
    "patterns": [
      ".kiro/specs/**/*.md",
      ".kiro/steering/**/*.md",
      ".kiro/settings/github.json"
    ],
    "branches": ["main", "develop", "feature/*"]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "tool": "tools/faangai-github-sync.ps1",
    "arguments": ["-Action", "sync-specs", "-AutoCreate"],
    "prompt": "ðŸ”„ FAANGAI SPECS MODIFIED - SYNC WITH GITHUB\n\nFAANGAI specification files have been updated. Execute GitHub synchronization:\n\n1. **Identify changed specs**: Extract modified .kiro/specs/**/*.md files\n2. **Process tasks.md files**: Convert task checkboxes to GitHub issues\n3. **Update requirements.md**: Create or update epic issues\n4. **Sync design.md**: Update design documentation issues\n5. **Project board updates**: Move items to appropriate status columns\n\n**GitHub Actions**:\n- Create issues for new tasks: `gh issue create --title \"Task\" --label \"faangai,task\"`\n- Update completed tasks: `gh issue edit ISSUE_NUMBER --add-label \"completed\"`\n- Link related issues: Connect tasks to requirements and design\n- Update project board: Move items based on progress\n\n**Sync Mapping**:\n- `[ ]` tasks â†’ Open GitHub issues\n- `[x]` tasks â†’ Completed GitHub issues\n- Requirements â†’ Epic issues with \"requirements\" label\n- Design â†’ Documentation issues with \"design\" label\n\n**Validation Steps**:\n1. Check GitHub CLI availability: `gh auth status`\n2. Verify repository connection: `gh repo view`\n3. Validate project board access: `gh project list`\n4. Confirm issue creation permissions\n\n**Success Criteria**:\nâœ… Task items synchronized with GitHub issues\nâœ… Project board reflects current status\nâœ… Labels applied correctly (kiro, task, requirements, design)\nâœ… Issue linking maintained for traceability\nâœ… No duplicate issues created\n\nGenerate sync summary and execute GitHub CLI commands for manual review. Report any conflicts or manual actions required."
  }
}
